@invobj
#cycle 1
(The tourist guides describe Rederring's
City Hall as a "masterpiece of functional
architecture, with a crisp, efficient
interior."

In other words, it's utterly sterile.

The potted plants do nothing to
relieve the monotony of the interior
design, and the grey/cyan carpeting makes
Cleatle feel drowsy the moment he steps in
the door.

To the planners, this is the ideal
reaction. Citizens who enter angry, ready
to disembowel a clerk, are incapable
of mustering the energy needed to glare
at the receptionist.

The City Hall officials are happy with
this state of things, despite the
soporific nature of the furnishings, as
training new clerks is very expensive.

The clerks express the greatest approval.)
/i
