:touch
Ode to an Office Chair

(With all due apology to Edwin Arlington
Robinson)

You think the chair is rather low,
 And thus try to adjust it.
Attempts to turn the handle show
 That time and damp can rust it.
You strain, and fractures start to show.
The base snaps, and the bearings go!
And, at this point, it's clear, you know,
 That you managed to bust it.
#end

