@edwards
#cycle 1
#end
:touch
(There's something about Mr. Edwards that
reminds one of a dolphin. Perhaps it's his
long, projecting nose, or maybe the way
his hair is parted in such a manner as
to create the appearance of a hole in his
scalp. Of course, it could just be his
fondness for whistling at the most
inappropriate times.

In any case, whatever similarities Mr.
Edwards bears to a bottle-nosed dolphin,
it is quite clear that he is not one. 
Most dolphins do not wear a perpetual
expression of annoyance, and very few have
such a thick accent.)

Edwards: Yes?

Cleatle: I would like to submit a ballot
design.

Edwards: Well then, I guess you're out
of luck.

Cleatle: What?

Edwards: The deadline passed two hours
ago, so you can't scan yours in. A
committee will receive these ballots
tomorrow and decide which one to use then.

Cleatle: Can't you just let me scan this
in? It couldn't hurt you, could it?

Edwards: Rules are rules.

Cleatle: (Aside) I guess I'll just have
to find a way to get him out of his
office so I can scan in the hairball
ballot.

Cleatle: (Aloud) Mind if I use your phone?

Edwards: It doesn't work. Here's my e-mail
address, though, if you need to talk to
me. (Hands Cleatle business card.)

Cleatle: (reads) tuna@freemail.com.

Edwards: Yes. Now, if you have no further
business, I would appreciate it if you
left.
#give health 10
#zap touch
#end
:touch
Edwards: ...

Cleatle: Oh, never mind.
#end
:mailed
Ed's computer: You've got mail!

Edwards: Let's see... Uh, oh. I'd better
get down there right away.

(Mr. Edwards walks out of his office and
leaves. Of course, Cleatle can't see this,
as he is in a different room, so, for
all intents and purposes, Edwards has
disappeared, without leaving so much as
a red fake.)
#send all:edgone
#die
:nm
#end
:keys
#if not contact nm
#send invobj:okay
Cleatle: Did you lose these?

Edwards: What? Oh - no, I didn't.
#end
:pipe
#if not contact nm
#send invobj:okay
(The pipe blow knocks Edwards unconscious,
and Cleatle can now search his office.)

Edwards: What are you staring at me for?

Cleatle: Just daydreaming.
#end

