(This bookshelf is covered with a glass
panel, presumably to keep dust off the
dust jackets. Cleatle opens it and takes a
quick glance inside. Inside are several
books on management, programming, and
marine biology.

One book doesn't seem to quite fit in: a
book of riddles. Cleatle takes it out to
examine, and clumsily drops it. It falls
open to page 32, which is dog-eared and
clearly well-read.

The riddle on the page reads:

"Here lies a conductor
In reverie grim.
Long time he beat me,
In the end, I beat him.

What am I?"

Sadly, the answer is covered by a coffee
spill.)
